{"format":"tiptap/v1","updatedAt":"2026-06-21T00:40:56.054Z","doc":{"type":"doc","content":[{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompting agents"},{"type":"text","text":" is the evolution from simple instruction-following to "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"instructing autonomous systems"},{"type":"text","text":" that can read files, call APIs, make decisions, delegate to sub-agents, and recover from errors."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"The key shift:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"Prompt engineering used to dominate. Now, for agents working over long sessions or multiple turns, that's not enough. Context engineering = curating all the tokens that feed the agent.\""}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"What Prompting Agents Is"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"A well-designed agent prompt steers a system that reads files, calls APIs, makes decisions, delegates to sub-agents, recovers from errors, and iterates until it achieves its goal.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Agent capabilities:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Read files"},{"type":"text","text":" — Access local data\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Call APIs"},{"type":"text","text":" — External tools\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Make decisions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Autonomous reasoning\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Delegate"},{"type":"text","text":" — Sub-agents for tasks\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Recover"},{"type":"text","text":" — Error handling\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Iterate"},{"type":"text","text":" — Loop until goal"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context Engineering vs Prompt Engineering"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Context engineering refers to the set of strategies for curating and maintaining the optimal set of tokens (information) during LLM inference, rather than just focusing on the instruction text.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt engineering:"},{"type":"text","text":" Methods for writing instructions\n"},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Context engineering:"},{"type":"text","text":" Curating ALL tokens (prompts + history + tool outputs + external data)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key difference:"},{"type":"text","text":" Prompt engineering = instruction text only | Context engineering = all information tokens"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Core Components of Agent Prompts"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 1: Role Definition"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Role definition: Who are you? (e.g., 'You are a research analyst...').\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are an expert software engineer specializing in Python development.\nYour role is to write clean, efficient code and help users debug issues."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key elements:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Identity"},{"type":"text","text":" — Who the agent is\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Expertise"},{"type":"text","text":" — Domain specialization\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Purpose"},{"type":"text","text":" — What it does"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 2: Goal Articulation"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Goal articulation: What are you trying to achieve?\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Your goal is to:\n1. Analyze user requirements\n2. Design solution architecture\n3. Write implementation code\n4. Test and debug"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key elements:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Objective"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear goal\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Steps"},{"type":"text","text":" — Process breakdown\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Outcome"},{"type":"text","text":" — Expected result"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 3: Operational Boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Operational constraints: How should you respond? What not to do?\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Constraints:\n- DO NOT write code without understanding requirements first\n- DO NOT assume user preferences\n- DO use existing libraries when possible\n- DO ask clarifying questions when uncertain"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key elements:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Do's"},{"type":"text","text":" — Allowed actions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Don'ts"},{"type":"text","text":" — Forbidden actions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guidance"},{"type":"text","text":" — When to ask"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 4: Tool Definitions"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"For an AI agent, tools are its hands and eyes, allowing it to interact with its environment to get the work done.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"json"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Available tools:\n1. read_file(path) - Read file contents\n2. write_file(path, content) - Write to file\n3. search_web(query) - Search the web\n4. calculate(expression) - Perform math\n5. execute_command(cmd) - Run shell command"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Well-defined"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear purpose\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No overlap"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each tool unique\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token-efficient"},{"type":"text","text":" — Minimal output\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Precise"},{"type":"text","text":" — Accurate results"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 5: Output Format"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Output Format: Define the structure for responses.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Output format:\n1. Thought: Your reasoning\n2. Action: Tool call (JSON)\n3. Observation: Tool result\n4. Final Answer: Conclusion"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured formats:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"JSON"},{"type":"text","text":" — Machine-readable\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"YAML"},{"type":"text","text":" — Human-readable\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Markdown"},{"type":"text","text":" — Formatted text"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Component 6: Decision Guidance"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompting must enforce structure — YAML, JSON, or Markdown — so the system doesn't fall apart from parsing errors.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When to use tools:\n- Use read_file when accessing local data\n- Use search_web when needing external info\n- Use calculate for math problems\n- Use write_file when saving results\n\nWhen NOT to use tools:\n- General knowledge questions\n- Opinion-based requests\n- Creative writing tasks"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Prompting Frameworks for Agents"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework 1: ReAct (Reason + Act)"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"ReAct (Reason + Act) for agent prompting.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Core structure:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"Think-Act-Observe\" loop "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are an agent with access to tools.\n\nAvailable tools:\n1. read_file(path)\n2. write_file(path, content)\n3. search_web(query)\n4. calculate(expression)\n\nProcess (ReAct):\n1. Think: Reason about what to do next\n2. Act: Output tool call in JSON format\n3. Observe: Tool returns result\n4. Repeat until goal achieved\n\nExample:\nQuestion: Read the file and calculate the sum\n\nThought: I need to read the file first\nAction: {\"tool_call\": {\"name\": \"read_file\", \"arguments\": {\"path\": \"data.txt\"}}}\nObservation: \"10, 20, 30, 40, 50\"\n\nThought: I have the file contents, now I need to calculate the sum\nAction: {\"tool_call\": {\"name\": \"calculate\", \"arguments\": {\"expression\": \"10 + 20 + 30 + 40 + 50\"}}}\nObservation: 150\n\nThought: I have the result\nFinal Answer: The sum of numbers in data.txt is 150."}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key steps:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Think"},{"type":"text","text":" — Reasoning about next step "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"},{"type":"text","text":"\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Act"},{"type":"text","text":" — Structured tool call "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"},{"type":"text","text":"\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Observe"},{"type":"text","text":" — Tool result returned "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"},{"type":"text","text":"\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Repeat"},{"type":"text","text":" — Loop until goal "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework 2: Multi-Agent Orchestration"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Multi-Agent orchestration to improve a prompt (using multiple different models).\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"System: Research Agent\nRole: Expert researcher\nGoal: Gather credible sources on X\nOutput: Summary with citations\n\nSystem: Writer Agent\nRole: Professional writer\nGoal: Craft concise LinkedIn post\nOutput: Final post using research\n\nSystem: Reviewer Agent\nRole: Quality assurance\nGoal: Evaluate and suggest improvements\nOutput: Critique and recommendations\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Research Agent gathers sources\n2. Writer Agent creates post\n3. Reviewer Agent evaluates\n4. Loop 2-3 if improvements needed"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key features:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distinct roles"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each agent specialized\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured output"},{"type":"text","text":" — Format enforcement\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Orchestration"},{"type":"text","text":" — Ordered workflow"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework 3: Sub-Agent Architecture"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Sub-Agent Architectures: For highly complex tasks, a single AI agent can delegate work to specialized sub-agents.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Lead Agent:\n  Role: Project coordinator\n  Goal: Synthesize results from sub-agents\n  Output: Final summary\n\nSub-Agent 1 (Research):\n  Role: Information gatherer\n  Goal: Find relevant sources\n  Output: Research summary\n\nSub-Agent 2 (Analysis):\n  Role: Data analyst\n  Goal: Analyze findings\n  Output: Analysis report\n\nSub-Agent 3 (Writing):\n  Role: Content creator\n  Goal: Write final document\n  Output: Draft content\n\nProcess:\n1. Lead Agent assigns tasks to sub-agents\n2. Sub-agents work independently\n3. Sub-agents return condensed summaries\n4. Lead Agent synthesizes results"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specialization"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each sub-agent deep dive\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Condensed output"},{"type":"text","text":" — Brief summaries\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Synthesis"},{"type":"text","text":" — Lead agent integrates"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework 4: Compaction for Long-Horizon Tasks"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Compaction: This involves summarizing a long conversation or work history, filtering the most critical details, and starting a new session with that compressed summary.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Session 1:\n- Full conversation log\n- Work history\n- All decisions\n\nAction: Compaction\n  - Summarize conversation\n  - Filter critical details\n  - Discard unnecessary info\n\nSession 2:\n- Compressed summary from Session 1\n- New context\n- Continue work\n\nProcess:\nFor tasks requiring extended work:\n1. Work through session\n2. When approaching token limit:\n   - Summarize key decisions\n   - Filter unresolved issues\n   - Discard noise\n3. Start new session with summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Preserves key info"},{"type":"text","text":" — Critical decisions\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Discards noise"},{"type":"text","text":" — Unnecessary details\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Maintains coherence"},{"type":"text","text":" — Across sessions"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Framework 5: Structured Note-Taking"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Structured Note-Taking / Agentic Memory: This technique allows an AI agent to maintain an external 'memory,' like a digital notepad.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"External Memory (notepad.txt):\n- Key findings\n- To-do lists\n- Strategic notes\n- Decisions made\n- Unresolved issues\n\nUsage:\n1. When agent finds important info:\n   - Write to notepad.txt\n2. When agent needs context:\n   - Read from notepad.txt\n3. Periodically:\n   - Summarize and update\n\nBenefits:\n- Persistent memory without context clutter\n- Pull back into context when needed\n- Maintain state across sessions"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Benefits:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Persistent memory"},{"type":"text","text":" — Outside context window\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clean working memory"},{"type":"text","text":" — No clutter\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pull when needed"},{"type":"text","text":" — On-demand retrieval"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Best Practices for Agent Prompting"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"1. Write Clear and Balanced Prompts"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"System prompts need to hit a 'Goldilocks zone,' avoiding overly strict hardcoded logic that makes the system less reliable. At the same time, system prompts should not be too vague, which can leave the AI without a clear direction.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Balance:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too strict"},{"type":"text","text":" — Avoid brittle if-else logic\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too vague"},{"type":"text","text":" — Provide clear direction\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specific guidance"},{"type":"text","text":" — Heuristics without micromanagement"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"2. Design Efficient Tools"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Tools should be short, descriptive, focused. They shouldn't be confusing or overlapping.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Short"},{"type":"text","text":" — Minimal tokens\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Descriptive"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear purpose\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Focused"},{"type":"text","text":" — Specific function\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"No overlap"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each tool unique"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"3. Just-in-Time Context Retrieval"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Instead of overwhelming the AI model by loading all potentially relevant data upfront, a more effective strategy is to let the AI agent dynamically pull in information as needed.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Approach:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Don't preload"},{"type":"text","text":" — Load when needed\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dynamic pull"},{"type":"text","text":" — On-demand retrieval\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Mirrors human cognition"},{"type":"text","text":" — Recall when required\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clean working memory"},{"type":"text","text":" — Focused attention"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Implementation:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Keep identifiers:\n- File paths\n- Queries\n- Metadata\n\nFetch when needed:\n- When task requires it\n- When context is missing\n- When decision depends on it"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"4. System Prompts at Right Altitude"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"System prompts should be extremely clear and use simple, direct language that presents ideas at the right altitude for the agent.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Altitude guidelines:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too low"},{"type":"text","text":" — Avoid micromanagement\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Not too high"},{"type":"text","text":" — Provide clear direction\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Right altitude"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear instructions, structured sections"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structure:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"System Prompt:\n- Background: Context and purpose\n- Tools: Available capabilities\n- Responsibilities: What to do\n- Output Format: Response structure"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5. Manage History Effectively"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Avoid raw accumulation; use truncation, summarization, or structured state tracking to prevent bloat and error propagation.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Methods:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Truncation"},{"type":"text","text":" — Keep recent only\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Summarization"},{"type":"text","text":" — Compress old\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured state"},{"type":"text","text":" — Track key info"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6. Token Budgeting"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Manage tokens across full agent loops; prioritize trimming tool outputs and maintain ~60–80% utilization.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Guidelines:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"60-80% utilization"},{"type":"text","text":" — Don't max out\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Trim tool outputs"},{"type":"text","text":" — Prioritize\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Dynamic allocation"},{"type":"text","text":" — Simple tasks minimal, complex tasks more"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"7. Role Specialization"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Assign distinct roles to agents and ensure prompts emphasize their specific expertise. Overlap = confusion.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Distinct roles"},{"type":"text","text":" — No overlap\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Specific expertise"},{"type":"text","text":" — Emphasize\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Clear boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":" — Each agent focused"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"8. Enforce Structure"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Prompting must enforce structure — YAML, JSON, or Markdown — so the system doesn't fall apart from parsing errors.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured formats:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"JSON"},{"type":"text","text":" — Machine-readable\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"YAML"},{"type":"text","text":" — Human-readable\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Markdown"},{"type":"text","text":" — Formatted"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"9. Define Escalation Paths"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Some agents need instructions for what to do when they're unsure. Prompting for escalation paths ('If you're not confident, pass it back to the planner') reduces silent failure.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Template:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"text"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"When unsure:\n- If not confident: Pass back to planner\n- If stuck: Ask for clarification\n- If blocked: Report to coordinator"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10. Treat Context as Limited Budget"},{"type":"text","text":" ⭐"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"When you design agents, treat each piece of context (history, tools, system instructions) as a limited budget. Prune aggressively.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Pruning:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Aggressive"},{"type":"text","text":" — Remove stale\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Only relevant"},{"type":"text","text":" — Keep what matters\n- "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Track usage"},{"type":"text","text":" — Monitor budget"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Real-World Agent Examples"}]},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 1: Research Agent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are an expert researcher.\n\nRole: Gather credible sources on a topic\n\nGoal: Collect and summarize key insights\n\nAvailable tools:\n1. search_web(query) - Search for information\n2. read_url(url) - Extract page content\n3. summarize(text) - Create summary\n\nProcess (ReAct):\n1. Think: Reason about next step\n2. Act: Call tool (JSON)\n3. Observe: Get result\n4. Repeat until comprehensive\n\nOutput format:\n- Key findings (bullet points)\n- Sources (with URLs)\n- Summary (2-3 paragraphs)\n\nQuestion: What are the latest trends in AI?"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 2: Code Review Agent"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"You are a senior software engineer.\n\nRole: Review code for quality and bugs\n\nGoal: Identify issues and suggest improvements\n\nAvailable tools:\n1. read_file(path) - Read code\n2. analyze_code(code) - Static analysis\n3. suggest_fix(code, issue) - Generate fix\n\nProcess:\n1. Read file\n2. Analyze for issues\n3. Suggest fixes\n4. Generate report\n\nOutput format:\n## Issues Found\n- [Issue 1]: Description\n- [Issue 2]: Description\n\n## Suggested Fixes\n- [Fix 1]: Code\n- [Fix 2]: Code\n\n## Recommendations\n- [Recommendation 1]\n- [Recommendation 2]"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":3},"content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Example 3: Multi-Agent Workflow"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompt System:"}]},{"type":"codeBlock","attrs":{"language":"yaml"},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Agent 1: Planner\n  Role: Task coordinator\n  Goal: Break down complex tasks\n  Output: Task list with dependencies\n\nAgent 2: Researcher\n  Role: Information gatherer\n  Goal: Find relevant data\n  Output: Research summary\n\nAgent 3: Writer\n  Role: Content creator\n  Goal: Create final document\n  Output: Draft content\n\nAgent 4: Reviewer\n  Role: Quality assurance\n  Goal: Evaluate and improve\n  Output: Critique and recommendations\n\nWorkflow:\n1. Planner breaks down task\n2. Researcher gathers data\n3. Writer creates content\n4. Reviewer evaluates\n5. If improvements needed:\n   - Loop 3-4\n6. When satisfied:\n   - Final output"}]},{"type":"horizontalRule"},{"type":"heading","attrs":{"level":2},"content":[{"type":"text","text":"Summary"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Prompting agents"},{"type":"text","text":" instructs autonomous systems that can read files, call APIs, make decisions, delegate, recover, and iterate:"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Definition:"},{"type":"text","text":" \"A well-designed agent prompt steers a system that reads files, calls APIs, makes decisions, delegates to sub-agents, recovers from errors, and iterates until it achieves its goal.\""}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Key shift:"},{"type":"text","text":" Prompt engineering → Context engineering (curating ALL tokens)"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"6 core components:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role definition"},{"type":"text","text":" — Who the agent is\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Goal articulation"},{"type":"text","text":" — What to achieve\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Operational boundaries"},{"type":"text","text":" — Do's/don'ts\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Tool definitions"},{"type":"text","text":" — Available capabilities\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Output format"},{"type":"text","text":" — Response structure\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Decision guidance"},{"type":"text","text":" — When to use tools"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"5 prompting frameworks:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"ReAct"},{"type":"text","text":" — Think-Act-Observe loop "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"link","attrs":{"href":"https://zhu.codes/papers/llmtools.pdf","target":"_blank","rel":"noopener noreferrer nofollow","class":"text-brand-600 underline dark:text-brand-400","title":null}}],"text":"zhu"},{"type":"text","text":"\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Multi-Agent orchestration"},{"type":"text","text":" — Multiple agents, ordered workflow\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Sub-Agent architecture"},{"type":"text","text":" — Delegate to specialized agents\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Compaction"},{"type":"text","text":" — Summarize long conversations\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Structured note-taking"},{"type":"text","text":" — External memory"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"10 best practices:"},{"type":"text","text":"\n1. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Write clear, balanced prompts"},{"type":"text","text":" — Goldilocks zone\n2. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Design efficient tools"},{"type":"text","text":" — Short, descriptive, focused\n3. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Just-in-time retrieval"},{"type":"text","text":" — Load when needed\n4. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"System prompts at right altitude"},{"type":"text","text":" — Clear, structured\n5. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Manage history"},{"type":"text","text":" — Truncate, summarize\n6. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Token budgeting"},{"type":"text","text":" — 60-80% utilization\n7. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Role specialization"},{"type":"text","text":" — Distinct, no overlap\n8. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Enforce structure"},{"type":"text","text":" — JSON, YAML, Markdown\n9. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Define escalation paths"},{"type":"text","text":" — Handle uncertainty\n10. "},{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"Treat context as budget"},{"type":"text","text":" — Prune aggressively"}]},{"type":"paragraph","content":[{"type":"text","marks":[{"type":"bold"}],"text":"\"Context isn't about stuffing more information — it's about choosing what matters most, when it matters.\""}]}]}}
